  <h1>Math Art: Picasso as a Mathematician</h1>
  <time datetime=2013-08-28T03:59:13Z class="post-date">Wed, Aug 28, 2013</time>
  <div id="attachment_70" style="width: 640px" class="wp-caption aligncenter">
  <a href="https://rs.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/picasso-and-the-bull.jpg"><img class="wp-image-70 size-full" src="https://rs.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/picasso-and-the-bull.jpg" alt="picasso-and-the-bull" width="630" height="412" srcset="https://rs.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/picasso-and-the-bull.jpg 630w, https://rs.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/picasso-and-the-bull-300x196.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px" /></a>
  
  <p class="wp-caption-text">
    Math art.
  </p>
</div>

<blockquote>
<p>I wanted to live deep and suck out all the marrow of life, to live so sturdily and Spartan-like as to put to rout all that was not life, to cut a broad swath and shave close, to drive life into a corner, and reduce it to its lowest terms.</p>

<p><span id="quote-attribute">Henry David Thoreau, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0083ZBUXU/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B0083ZBUXU&linkCode=as2&tag=rsio-20&linkId=WWKKDSZJVYKV43BB"><em>Walden</em></a></span></p>

<p>If people do not believe that mathematics is simple, it is only because they do not realize how complicated life is.</p>

<p><span id="quote-attribute"><a href="http://homepage.cs.uiowa.edu/~jorgen/vonneumannquotesource.html">John von Neumann</a></span></p>
</blockquote>

<p>Picasso drew <strong>math art</strong>: a bull in full and then simplified the figure to a few lines, to the essence of a bull. This is the role of mathematics in the sciences. She takes reality and distills it to its essence. She drives life into a corner and reduces it to its lowest terms.</p>

